body_html:
Package loading is done by traversing entries in sys.path until there's a
match. So if os.getcwd() and sys.path are identical between Python and
ipython, your package loading should be the same.

On Aug 2, 2016 7:38 PM, "Deepak" notifications@github.com wrote:

I thought that would be the case, but my Python path is set to
/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages. its where google/protobuf is.

—
